 In many less-developed countries, the early 
 farming-based research institutes were established 
 by (related to Europe) colonial powers and, during the first 
 half of this century, these institutes were staffed 
 with (ban from a country) (people who work to find information). On independence, 
 most former (groups of people or other living things) moved to replace (ban from a country)s with national (people who work to find information). In some countries, 
 this change happened slowly but in others it 
 was a more sudden process and caused major 
 disruptions in farming-based research programs. At 
