 While certainly not discounting the value of training (people who work to find information) to the PhD level, these (instances of watching, noticing, or making statements) would suggest that greater attention should 
 be given to the research information meeting and training 
 within BSc and especially MSc programs at local 
 universities rather than simply looking (for) a high 
 proportion of PhDs through training in other countries, par- 
 
